## SECTION 9 — WRITING INSTRUCTIONS

**POST GEN INSTRUCTION: Follow these rules for every paragraph of body copy.**

- This is conversion copy — every sentence moves the buyer toward a purchase decision
- Lead with buyer benefit, not product specs — specs support the benefit, they never lead
- Use buyer phrases from Section 5 naturally — "salon quality at a fraction of the cost," "simple, lightweight, forgiving," "perfect for stocking stuffers"
- Address the "is this a real deal?" objection early and directly — show the original prices and note they're the standard year-round price
- Address "which drill should I buy?" in the head-to-head section with a clear recommendation, not hedging
- Discount code information placed naturally near product CTAs and in the stacking section — not as a standalone promo paragraph
- **Primary keyword in `<strong>` tags every single mention — no exceptions**
- No editorial literary hooks — open sections with the buyer benefit or buying decision directly
- H2 sections are direct and short — buyers scan, they don't read long section intros
- Conclusion is a decision driver — not a summary
- Internal links placed mid-post after first product CTA only — anchor text natural and specific
- No related articles section — handled by site component
- **Language: American English only**
- **No banned AI phrases:** no "elevate," "seamlessly," "game-changing," "dive into," "transformative"
- **No long em dashes** — use commas or restructure sentences
- Sentence rhythm varies: short punchy sentences for key selling points, longer for context and objection-handling
- No "we tested" language — write as an informed editorial voice drawing on verified product specs and real buyer reviews
- Honest cons build trust — include them, then show why the product is still the right buy at this price
